\f0\b\fs42 \cf0 BIBLICAL NARRATIVES\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs30 \cf0 Scripture doesn\'92t hide envy\'92s devastation:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Cain & Abel (Genesis 4):
\f1\b0  Envy led to the first murder.\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Joseph\'92s Brothers (Genesis 37):
\f1\b0  Envy fractured a family for decades.\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Saul & David (1 Samuel 18):
\f1\b0  Envy consumed a king\'92s legacy.\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Pharisees (Matthew 27:18):
\f1\b0  Envy nailed Jesus to a cross.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The pattern is always the same: envy begins small. It ends deadly.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
