\f0\b\fs42 \cf0 CLOSING WORD\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs30 \cf0 Envy is subtle, slippery, and destructive. It rarely announces itself, but it always grows when fed.\
Comparison is its soil. Dissatisfaction is its fertilizer. Bitterness is its fruit.\
But Jesus calls us to a different way: gratitude, contentment, and celebration. To trust that His story for your life is good, even if it looks different than someone else\'92s.\
Don\'92t feed the alligator of envy. Starve it with gratitude. Kill it with celebration. Replace it with contentment in Christ.\
Because envy rots the bones \'97 but a heart at peace gives life.\
